    "Starting on May 22, 2023, attackers began downloading MIPS binaries over HTTP from 45.89.106[.]147 to Zyxel firewalls within a targeted energy sector organization.",
    "The downloaded binaries were identified as Mirai variants containing indicators of the Moobot flavor.",
    "After the malware was installed, the firewalls began communicating on port 56999/TCP (a known C2 port for Mirai variants) with a server at “www.joshan[.]pro,” which resolved to 185.44.81[.]147.",
    "The infected firewalls subsequently started participating in DDoS and SSH brute-force attacks against targets located in Hong Kong, the U.S., and Canada."
