  "operations": [
    "Cyber Sabotage/Disruptive Operations: APT44 is responsible for an intensive campaign of cyber disruptions, deploying wiper malware against a mix of civilian and military targets. Since February 2022, it has been responsible for almost all disruptive and destructive cyber attacks against Ukrainian CIKRs. These operations involve capabilities intended to disrupt industrial control and safety systems, including a new variant of Industroyer and Operational Technology (OT)-specific living-off-the-land attacks.",
    "Cyber Espionage/Military Enablement: The group increasingly conducts espionage, which appears to focus on mobile networks, devices, applications, and other technologies to intercept communications and gain tactical and operational battlefield advantages for Russian conventional military operations.",
    "Information Operations: APT44 uses front personas embedded in the pro-Russian Telegram ecosystem to attempt to shape the information environment and draw attention to the alleged impact of select cyber operations.",
    "General Scope: APT44 is actively engaged in the full spectrum of cyber espionage, attack, and influence operations."
  ]
}

{
  "role_and_utility": "CADDYWIPER is a disruptive file wiper written in C. Its function is to enumerate the file system physical drives and overwrite both file content and partitions with null bytes. It has both executable and shellcode variants.",
  "observed_usage_and_spread": "In the threat landscape, CADDYWIPER has been observed in destructive cyber operations (alongside INDUSTROYER.V2, SOLOSHRED, and AWFULSHRED), during sustained targeting and attacks, and in renewed campaigns of disruptive attacks, sometimes alongside a native MicroSCADA binary."
